@page "/privacy"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy â€” Chronicis</PageTitle>

<div class="static-page">
    <div class="static-page-content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM d, yyyy")</p>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>
                At Chronicis, we take your privacy seriously. This policy explains what 
                information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <h3>Account Information</h3>
            <p>
                When you create an account, we collect your email address, display name, 
                and profile picture from your authentication provider (Google, Discord, or Apple).
            </p>
            
            <h3>Content You Create</h3>
            <p>
                We store the articles, notes, and other content you create within Chronicis. 
                This content is associated with your account and is not shared with other users 
                unless you explicitly choose to share it.
            </p>
            
            <h3>Usage Data</h3>
            <p>
                We collect basic usage data to improve our service, including page views, 
                feature usage, and error logs. This data is anonymized and aggregated.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide and maintain the Chronicis service</li>
                <li>To authenticate your identity and secure your account</li>
                <li>To improve our service based on usage patterns</li>
                <li>To communicate important updates about the service</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>Data Storage & Security</h2>
            <p>
                Your data is stored securely on Microsoft Azure servers. We use industry-standard 
                encryption for data in transit and at rest. We do not sell your data to third parties.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>AI Features</h2>
            <p>
                When you use AI-powered features like summary generation, your article content 
                is sent to Azure OpenAI for processing. This data is not used to train AI models 
                and is not retained after processing.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Access your personal data</li>
                <li>Export your content</li>
                <li>Delete your account and all associated data</li>
                <li>Opt out of non-essential communications</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>
                If you have questions about this privacy policy or your data, please contact us 
                through the feedback mechanisms in the application.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>
